com.jnape.palatable.lambda.lens

Interface Lens.Fixed<S,T,A,B,F extends Functor,FT extends Functor<T,F>,FB extends Functor<B,F>>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - the type of the "larger" value for reading
    T - the type of the "larger" value for putting
    A - the type of the "smaller" value that is read
    B - the type of the "smaller" update value
    F - the functor unification type between FT and FB
    FT - the type of the lifted T
    FB - the type of the lifted B
    All Superinterfaces:
    Applicative<Fn1<S,FT>,Fn1<Function<? super A,? extends FB>,?>>, Fn1<Function<? super A,? extends FB>,Fn1<S,FT>>, Fn2<Function<? super A,? extends FB>,S,FT>, Function<Function<? super A,? extends FB>,Fn1<S,FT>>, Functor<Fn1<S,FT>,Fn1<Function<? super A,? extends FB>,?>>, Profunctor<Function<? super A,? extends FB>,Fn1<S,FT>,Fn1>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Lens.Simple.Fixed<S,A,F,FS,FA>
    Enclosing interface:
    Lens<S,T,A,B>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface Lens.Fixed<S,T,A,B,F extends Functor,FT extends Functor<T,F>,FB extends Functor<B,F>>
extends Fn2<Function<? super A,? extends FB>,S,FT>
    A lens that has been fixed to a functor. Because the lens is no longer polymorphic, it can additionally be safely represented as an Fn2.
